prompt:
Add a public function called AllPositive to Contracts.calr that takes an array of i32 and returns bool. Use a forall quantifier in the postcondition to express that if the result is true, all elements are positive.

Use this exact Calor forall quantifier syntax:
§F{f001:AllPositive:pub}
  §I{i32[]:arr}
  §O{bool}
  §S (-> result (forall ((i i32)) (-> (and (>= i 0) (< i (len arr))) (> (at arr i) 0))))
  §B{allPos} true
  §L{l001:i:0:(len arr):1}
    §IF{if001} (<= (at arr i) 0)
      §ASSIGN allPos false
    §/I{if001}
  §/L{l001}
  §R allPos
§/F{f001}

The (forall ((var type)) body) syntax:
- Declares a universally quantified variable
- var:type binds the variable with its type
- body is the condition that must hold for all values
- Use (-> p q) for implication (if p then q)
